original: Johansson, Gustaf Artur, distriktsveterinär, Norrköping, f. 4/3’/94 i Flo, Skarab. 1., av Anders J. o. Johanna Andersson. G. 30 m. Lisa Käck. Barn: Ulla Britta f. 30, Ingrid 32. — Stud:-ex. i Vänersborg 12, veter :kand. 15, veter:ex. 18. Distr:veter. i Arvidsjaur 21, i Öjebyn 22, i Götene 26, i Kvänum 29 o. i Norrköp. sed. 37.
translated: Johansson, Gustaf Artur, district veterinarian, Norrköping, born on March 4th, 1894 in Flo, Skaraborg County, son of Anders J. and Johanna Andersson. Married in 1930 to Lisa Käck. Children: Ulla Britta (born 1930) and Ingrid (born 1932). He completed his secondary education in Vänersborg in 1912, received his degree in veterinary science in 1915, and became a licensed veterinarian in 1918. He worked as a district veterinarian in Arvidsjaur starting in 1921, Öjebyn in 1922, Götene in 1926, Kvänum in 1929, and in Norrköping from 1937 onwards.
